.TH bcheckrc 8
.SH NAME
\*Lbcheckrc\*O \- Command script for checking and mounting local file systems
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
.sS
\*L/sbin/bcheckrc\*O
.sE
.SH DESCRIPTION
.iX "bcheckrc command"
.PP
The \*Lbcheckrc\*O script controls the checking and mounting of local file
systems during system startup.
.PP
An entry in the \*Linittab\*O file causes the system to execute the
\*Lbcheckrc\*O run commands, for example:
.oS
fs:23:wait:/sbin/bcheckrc < /dev/console > /dev/console 2>&1
.oE
.PP
The \*Lbcheckrc\*O script performs the following operations:
.ML
.LI
Checks the local file systems listed in \*L/etc/fstab\*O for consistency
.IP
Runs \*Lfsck\*O with the \*L-p\*O option to preen all disks of minor
inconsistencies resulting from the last system shutdown and to check for
serious inconsistencies caused by hardhard or software failure.
.LI
Changes the root file system from read-only to read-write
.LI
Mounts local file systems listed in \*L/etc/fstab\*O
.LE
.SH FILES
.VL
.LI "\*L/sbin/bcheckrc\*O"
Specifies the command path
.LE
.SH RELATED INFORMATION
.PP
